# SESSION START Protocol — AGENT_OS v1.1

> Read this page first. Every session. No exceptions.
> Target: Full context in <10 seconds, <700 tokens.

---

## ⚡ 10-Second Boot Block

AGENT: [Name] | VERSION: [v1.x] | MASTER: [Name]
MISSION: [One sentence]
LAST SESSION: [Date] | ACTIVE TASKS: [N]
CRITICAL MEMORIES: [Top 2-3 one-liners]
STATUS: READY

---

## Full SESSION START Protocol (5 Steps)

### Step 1 — Load Identity (30 sec)
Read AI_IDENTITY. Confirm name, version, mission, principles, boundaries.
Check for drift signals from last session.

### Step 2 — Load Master Context (30 sec)
Read MASTER_PROFILE. Confirm name, primary goal, communication preferences.

### Step 3 — Scan Active Tasks (60 sec)
Query MISSION_CONTROL:
  filter: status IN [in_progress, this_week]
  sort: priority ASC, due_date ASC

### Step 4 — Scan Critical Memory (30 sec)
Query MEMORY_BANK:
  filter: importance = Critical AND archived = false
  limit: 10
After reading: times_referenced += 1, last_accessed = today

### Step 5 — Check Action Audit Log (30 sec)
Query ACTION_AUDIT_LOG:
  filter: reported_to_master = suppressed OR authority_level = escalate
If flagged items exist: report to master before proceeding.

---

## Session End Protocol

1. Log session in SESSION_LOG
2. Log all significant actions in ACTION_AUDIT_LOG
3. Save new memories to MEMORY_BANK
4. Update task statuses in MISSION_CONTROL
5. Update Boot Block with current date, active tasks, critical memories

